items.title: China Evergrande Delisted From Hong Kong Stock Exchange
items.description: China Evergrande, delisted from the Hong Kong Stock Exchange on Monday, leaves behind a giant pile of debt and a long line of desperate creditors.

items.title: Katherine LaNasa Earned Her Role in ‘The Pitt’ the Hard Way
items.description: The actress received an Emmy nod for her performance as a seasoned E.R. nurse, a woman who has seen it all and lived to keep fighting. So has LaNasa.

items.title: Expecting on the Front Lines: Motherhood in Ukraine’s Military
items.description: Pregnant Ukrainian soldiers say they are fighting for the future of their country and for their children.

items.title: The Typical American College Student Is Not Who You Think
items.description: As a fight over the future of elite higher education consumes university leaders and politicians, most college students live in a very different world...

items.title: Philadelphia Transit Cuts Take Hold, and Commuters Begin to Feel the Pain
items.description: A budget shortfall has led the city’s transit authority to cut its bus and rail services by 20 percent.
